				<link>http://www.businessinsider.com/c/52f2d8a269bedd607e4c8ce2</link>
				<description>Bitcoins would not be worth 3x the amount. The only factor driving deflation would be lost coins, which would give us extremely slow deflation.

Also, if you are comparing USD to BTC, BTC will always &quot;gain value&quot;, not because it is actually is gaining value but because the dollar is being inflated. If you see BTC being the dominant currency (as it should be because it is far more stable) and watch the price of paper dollars drop as they print them, then you get a clearer picture of whats going on.</description>                            
