				<link>http://www.businessinsider.com/c/52f25bda6bb3f70723c251ab</link>
				<description>Let's say I pay someone a salary of Y bitcoins resulting in a profit of let's say 2x that amount a year from now.
Why would I do that if those bitcoins will at the same time be worth 3x the amount a year from now.

If I want to pay for work etc, it makes much more sense for me to pay in dollars. That won't lead to any bitcoins ending up in the worker's pocket and preventing widespread use.

The worker on his part won't care how you send the dollars, but I'm pretty sure he doesn't want to be charged an extra 10% in currency conversion fees at a shady exchange.</description>                            
